Key Match Events: The Rockets tied it with an 18-2 run to open the fourth quarter
Jonathan Kuminga scored the first two baskets of overtime to make it 123-119
Aaron Holiday stole the ball from Draymond Green and he fouled out a few seconds later
Tari Eason made two free throws after that to send it to overtime
Post-Match Reflections: The Warriors continued to win without Steph Curry, improving to 5-1 this season.
The team said he will be re-evaluated Sunday to see how much longer he’ll be out.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Warriors led by 31 points in the first half
Golden State’s 14th straight-regular season win over the Rockets and the eighth in a row in Houston
Houston made just 1 of 12 shots in overtime
Others: Andrew Wiggins added 15 points for Golden State in his return after missing two games with a strained back
